I want to intercept the `phx:updateChart` event in the `mounted` lifecycle hook of a LiveView component and update the chart data accordingly. The chart is created using Chart.js, and I want to ensure that the chart updates correctly when new data is received.
```js saas/assets/js/hooks/chart.js
import Chart from "chart.js/auto";

export default {
  mounted() {
    const ctx = this.el;
    new Chart(ctx, {
      type: "bar",
      data: {
        labels: ["Red", "Blue", "Yellow", "Green", "Purple", "Orange"],
        datasets: [
          {
            label: "# of Votes",
            data: [12, 19, 3, 5, 2, 3],
            borderWidth: 1,
          },
        ],
      },
      options: {
        scales: {
          y: {
            beginAtZero: true,
          },
        },
      },
    });

    window.addEventListener(`phx:updateChart.${this.el.id}`, this.updateData);
  },

  destroyed() {
    window.removeEventListener(
      `phx:updateChart.${this.el.id}`,
      this.updateData,
    );
  },

  updateData(newData) {
    this.chart.data.datasets[0].data = newData;
    this.chart.update();
  },
};
```


I want to send event `phx:updateChart` from the LiveView component to the JavaScript hook when new data is available. The event should include the new data for the chart.

